Bonjour [Name,fallback=],

Je suis CTO à Visage, une start-up basée à San Francisco et après une levée de fonds, nous avons élu domicile à Nantes pour l'équipe engineering.

Je cherche un Solutions Engineer pour travailler en étroite collaboration avec notre plus gros client et en profiter pour adapter notre plateforme aux entreprises de 10000 personnes et + pour réinventer le recrutement.

Je cherche quelqu'un qui sait se mettre dans la peau des utilisateurs,  est habitué à concevoir des MVP puis à industrialiser en collaboration étroite avec un client et l'équipe de dev, de préférence avec des bases solides en Full Stack JS. Est ce que ça vous dirait d'en discuter ?

Salaire compétitif, bureaux en plein centre au start-up Palace, horaires flexibles, possibilité de bosser de temps en temps en remote, et des stock options dans une start-up en pleine croissance!

Let me know !

Emmanuel Marboeuf
Co-founder & CTO - Visage 
 

Visage is a venture-backed startup based in San Francisco. Our crowdSOURCING Platform combines the expertise of a network of independent and in-house sourcers, and unique algorithms to deliver high-quality candidates profiles to employers worldwide within 24 hours.

 

Visage has raised over $4M in funding from top tier investors in the US. Whilst the company is already profitable, we are gearing ourselves for a Series A by the middle of 2020 with a view to building a team of 50 (currently 15). We work with over 45 clients including house names such as Siemens, Orange, and Sanofi. Our annual revenue is in excess of $1M.

Hi [Name,fallback=],
 
I noticed your profile while researching talented individuals to fill Mortgage Loan Originator (MLO) roles on our Consumer Direct Team nationwide with focus on our Charlotte, NC location. I’m reaching out to introduce myself and ask if you’re open to a conversation where I can share some things that may be appealing to you as an MLO. For example:
  • Aggressive compensation.  $2500 monthly base plus commission. 
    • 1-5 units = 45 bps on total volume
    • 6-8 units = 60 bps on total volume
    • 9+ units = 75 bps on total volume
    • 75 bps on self-generated business
  • We provide 8-10 leads a day that are a blend of portfolio retention & aggregated leads
  • Refined operations process with an average lock to fund of 33 days
  • Heavily capitalized company that is stable and experiencing incredible growth
  • Superior technology including Velocify; Encompass; Blend (digital app); Dial-IQ & Automated Email Marketing
  • Diverse product mix with Non-QM retail and second lien products available
  • Originate in 47 States
  • Will pay for licensing 

We have amazing people, lead resources and technology that make life easier on you as a loan originator and more importantly, your clients. Please let me know if you’re interested in exploring this opportunity a bit further and we can set up a time to have an initial conversation.

Kind Regards,
 

Cliff Mclaughlin

Vice President, Talent Acquisition

5800 Tennyson Parkway, Suite 450

Plano, TX

www.fgmc.com

Are you ready to accelerate your career, develop your HR experience and work for a world-leading recruitment company?

 

Cielo is launching a Night Shift in our new state of the art offices in RCBC Plaza Makati to provide the highest levels of live recruitment support to our US Recruiters, Hiring Managers and Candidates.

We are looking for Impression Centre Agents to provide live customer call support for our candidates – this may be providing updates on their application, helping arrange interviews or contacting recruiters to further assist with the candidate – we want to make sure our candidates always have someone who is available to help them through the recruitment process and answer any questions they may have.

Cielo is the world’s leading strategic Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO) partner with an impressive history of industry recognition - Cielo has consistently been ranked in the top 3 global rankings by HRO Today RPO Baker’s Dozen listing, Peak Matrix Leader placement by Everest Group and Industry Leader designation by NelsonHall.

Our new Manila Night Shift operation will form a key part of our future expansion and will provide exceptional growth opportunities for future career development and progression – Cielo has invested significantly in the new state of the art offices and ensuring that we provide the best possible facilities, culture and opportunities to our teams.

Given your expertise, I'm reaching out to you regarding a (Sr.) Account Executive opportunity for Jumio - this role will be remote based to cover Toronoto territory, specifically focused in the Financial Services sector.     Expanding the Sales team is critical to the success of Jumio - you will be responsible for hunting opportunities, managing the sales cycles and negotiating successful contracts in order to commence long term partnerships with new clients.

At Jumio, we solve the largest problem for businesses online: digital identity is meaningless without knowing real-world identity. As the leading Trusted Identity as a Service provider, and Frost & Sullivan’s Biometric Company of the Year, we allow hundreds of Enterprises to know and trust their customers.  With a global footprint, we’re expanding the team to meet strong client demand across a range of industries including Fintech, Financial Services (Banking/Insurance) and Gaming.

To date, Jumio has over 350 global blue-chip clients - serving some of the largest web properties on the planet!

Should you or someone you know be interested in learning more, I would welcome the conversation.

Best,
